0.user_question: Mike is at the library helping put away books. There are 82 book to put away total but a librarian takes 10 of them and leaves Mike with the rest. If he can fit 9 books on a shelf, how many shelves will he need?

ost_step.1: Determine the number of books Mike is responsible for putting away after the librarian takes 10 of them. Originally there were 82 books to put away, so subtracting the 10 taken by the librarian leaves Mike with 82 - 10 = 72 books to put away.

direct_answer.text:
Mike was left with 72 books to put away. Since he can fit 9 books per shelf:

To find out how many shelves he needs, divide the number of books he's responsible for by the capacity of a shelf. That is, \(72 \div 9\).

So, \(72 \div 9 = 8\). This means Mike needs 8 shelves to put away all the books. The answer is: 8.
